<TITLE> Verdicts on Shahjahan Siraj, family in three tax-doge cases Wednesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 28 (bdnews24.com) -- The verdicts of three separate cases of tax evasion against former minister Shahjahan Siraj, wife Rabeya Haider and son Rajib Siraj would be pronounced Wednesday. The verdicts in another four separate cases of tax dodge against Rajib Siraj, nicknamed Apu, have been set for Sept 5. Judge Shamsunnahar Begum of the Special Judge's Court-4, sited at the Sangsad Bhaban, Tuesday fixed the date for the verdicts after presentation of arguments by the state side. The National Board of Revenue on July 16 filed 11 separate cases against Shahjahan Siraj, Rabeya Haider, popularly known as Rabeya Siraj, and their son accusing them of evading income tax. All the accused in the cases are on the run. Rabeya on August 27 was jailed for 32 years in four separate cases of tax evasion and suppressing tax-related information. On the same accusation, her daughter-in-law Farzana Khan was sentenced to six years in jail on Aug 15 in her absence. bdnew
